[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      488[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Regulatory pathway is unclear.** An RL agent that recommends treatment modifications is a clinical decision support tool at minimum, possibly a medical device depending on how autonomous it becomes. The regulatory pathway depends on how the system is positioned. If it meets the four criteria for non-device Clinical Decision Support under the 21st Century Cures Act (Section 3060): displays information, intended for clinician use, clinician can independently review the basis for the recommendation, and not intended to replace clinical judgment, it may be exempt from FDA device regulation entirely. If it doesn't qualify for the CDS exemption (for example, if it becomes more autonomous), De Novo classification is more likely than 510(k) given the absence of a predicate device. The FDA's Predetermined Change Control Plan framework is relevant for the periodic retraining aspect. Consult regulatory counsel early; the classification decision shapes the entire development and validation strategy.
